.TH ELECTORAL-SIM 1 "December 2024" "electoral-sim 0.0.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
electoral-sim \- High-performance agent-based electoral simulation toolkit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B electoral-sim
[\fB\-h\fR] [\fB\-\-version\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B electoral-sim
is a modular agent-based modeling toolkit for simulating electoral systems, voter behavior, and political dynamics. Built on Mesa with Polars DataFrames, it supports 1M+ voters with vectorized operations and Numba JIT acceleration.

The toolkit provides:
.IP \(bu 2
Multiple electoral systems (FPTP, PR, IRV, STV)
.IP \(bu 2
11 country presets + EU Parliament
.IP \(bu 2
Advanced voter behavior models (proximity, valence, strategic voting)
.IP \(bu 2
Opinion dynamics on social networks
.IP \(bu 2
Coalition and government stability simulation
.IP \(bu 2
Comprehensive metrics (Gallagher Index, ENP, VSE, etc.)
.IP \(bu 2
Batch parameter sweeping for sensitivity analysis

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B run
Run a single election simulation with custom or preset parameters
.TP
.B batch  
Execute multiple simulations with parameter sweeps for sensitivity analysis
.TP
.B list-presets
List all available country and region electoral system presets

.SH OPTIONS
.SS General Options
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show program version and exit

.SS Run Command Options
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-voters " \fINUMBER\fR"
Number of voters (default: 100,000)
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-constituencies " \fINUMBER\fR"
Number of constituencies (default: 10)
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-system " \fISYSTEM\fR"
Electoral system: FPTP, PR, IRV, or STV (default: FPTP)
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-allocation " \fIMETHOD\fR"
PR allocation method: dhondt, sainte_lague, hare, or droop (default: dhondt)
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-threshold " \fIFLOAT\fR"
Electoral threshold 0-1, e.g., 0.05 for 5% (default: 0)
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-preset " \fICOUNTRY\fR"
Use country preset (overrides other parameters). Available: india, usa, uk, germany, france, japan, brazil, australia_house, australia_senate, south_africa, eu
.TP
.B \-\-seed \fINUMBER\fR
Random seed for reproducibility
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " \fIFILE\fR"
Output file path (JSON format)
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress console output

.SS Batch Command Options
.TP
.B \-\-config \fIFILE\fR
JSON configuration file for batch run (required)
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " \fIFILE\fR"
Output file: CSV, Parquet, or JSON (required)
.TP
.B \-\-summary \fIFILE\fR
Optional summary statistics output file
.TP
.BR \-j ", " \-\-jobs " \fINUMBER\fR"
Number of parallel workers (default: 1)
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress progress output

.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic Simulation
.PP
.nf
.RS
electoral-sim run --voters 50000 --constituencies 10
.RE
.fi
.PP
Use a country preset:
.PP
.nf
.RS
electoral-sim run --preset india --voters 100000
.RE
.fi

.SS Proportional Representation
.PP
.nf
.RS
electoral-sim run --system PR --allocation sainte_lague --threshold 0.05
.RE
.fi

.SS Save Results
.PP
.nf
.RS
electoral-sim run --preset germany --output results.json
.RE
.fi

.SS List Available Presets
.PP
.nf
.RS
electoral-sim list-presets
.RE
.fi

.SS Batch Simulation with Parameter Sweep
.PP
Create a batch configuration file \fBbatch_config.json\fR:
.PP
.nf
.RS
{
  "parameters": {
    "n_voters": [10000, 50000, 100000],
    "temperature": [0.3, 0.5, 0.7],
    "economic_growth": [-0.02, 0.0, 0.02]
  },
  "fixed_params": {
    "n_constituencies": 10,
    "electoral_system": "FPTP"
  },
  "n_runs_per_config": 5,
  "n_jobs": 4
}
.RE
.fi
.PP
Run the batch simulation:
.PP
.nf
.RS
electoral-sim batch --config batch_config.json --output results.csv
.RE
.fi

